headshotImage.longCaption: Kieron Pollard player page headshot cutout, 2021

dismissalComment.html: 137 kph, middle and leg goes for a toss! Pollard, why would he go for a lap sweep? Well, possibly because there was no-one at fine leg. Either ways. he's more powerful down the ground. And this wasn't the ball to get cheeky. Only manages to give free passage to the ball as he gets down on one-knee outside off
full on off stump, he gets under the ball, a little too much actually. Slices it up into the air and Virat Kohli at long-off steadies himself under and reverse-cups it cleanly

and now he swings across the line. Why? That went through with the angle, and he would have been okay looking to hit straight again, but he went across the line and missed, and the ball crashed into the stumps

dismissalText.commentary: Ajinkya Rahane run out (Smith/Ramdin/Rampaul) 24 (22b 4x4 0x6 43m) SR: 109.09

dismissalComment.html: oh there's a run out, both batsmen at the same end! Rahane tapped the length ball on the pads between short fine leg and square leg, they took the first run quickly and Rahane wanted the second so he continued to run hard while Dhawan went back after taking a step and both were at the keeper's end, Rahane has to go back. The throw was at the keeper's end but Ramdin quickly threw it to Rampaul at the other end

dismissalText.commentary: Virat Kohli c Sammy b Taylor 2 (5b 0x4 0x6 7m) SR: 40

dismissalComment.html: this one straightens and Kohli's gone! He bowled it with the angle from outside off, it held its line a bit as Kohli went on the back foot to defend with an angled bat and the outside edge flew to Sammy at wide slip for a low catch near his right foot

dismissalText.commentary: Ambati Rayudu c Benn b Russell 13 (21b 1x4 0x6 33m) SR: 61.9

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, he's rushed down the track and miscued a swipe to mid-on. He's showed some good timing till now and he seems to know it as he walks back, head thrown back, but this time he has looked to force a drill down the ground. To horrible effects

dismissalText.commentary: Mohammed Shami b Rampaul 19 (17b 2x4 1x6 26m) SR: 111.76

commentTextItems.html: it's all over, finally! The yorker from Rampual wraps it up, he pitched it right on the base of leg stump as Shami made room and missed it

commentPostTextItems.html: MS Dhoni: It was a par score but it was a good wicket to bat on. Last few overs we bowled well to restrict them. At the start of the match if we were given 320-odd we should have got it. They bat really deep and have 6 bowlers with a part-timer. They have spinners, quick bowlers and are a balanced side. Dwayne Bravo and I know each other well. But with technology as well we can spot the weaknesses and do analysis of the opponents easily these days

Dwayne Bravo: It was a great team effort, credit to entire team especially to Samuels coming back to ODI team. Credit to the stand between him and Ramdin and the bowlers as well. I hope Simmons is fit for the next match but I'm ready to open for the team. It's well and good till we keep winning. Scoring over 320 is always good, we fell short by 15-20 runs and they bowled very well but great team effort from us.

Marlon Samuels is Man of the Match: After some injuries and surgery I didn't play much, got some form in CPL but didn't play much. I lost my coach also so I dedicate this to him. Ramdin is in good nick for the last year and he's been batting well. The communication and running between us went well between us.

Well, that's all from us for this ODI in Kochi. West Indies have taken a 1-0 lead and do join us on Saturday for the second match in Delhi at 1430 local time. Till then, it's goodbye and good luck from Vishal and Alagappan, ciao!

10.15pm That's a comprehensive win for West Indies to begin this tour after losing both their warm-up matches to India A. Smith gave a strong start, and that stand between Samuels and Ramdin took them past 300. India were definitely capable of chasing that, but some tight bowling from Rampaul, and disciplined lines from medium-pacers put India in trouble at 114 for 5. Samuels also got two wickets and whatever Ambrose said in the team huddle during the innings break seems to have worked

Jerome Taylor: I haven't played ODI cricket for a while and to come back with such a performance against a strong team gives confidence. When you can come out and perform, with a good team effort it keeps the dressing room positive.
Shubhank: "One thing Indian team should notice for the upcoming matches is that west indies have a good death bowling attach as rampaul was getting blockholes right."

Tajal: "Ever since Ambrose emerged on the sidelines for WI, the bowlers have been showing better discipline in their lines and length (overall control). There is no one who can drive that point across quite as good as the great Curtly Ambrose. He's a great presence in this team"

commentTextItems.html: full and just outside off, pushed to long-off with an open face for one more
clears his front leg, slaps the ball down the ground to mid-on
another one in the block hole, this one gets Shami's right toe as he made some room again. He looks in some pain, but is alright
superb yorker, straight towards Shami's toes as he made room but well outside the leg stump
Shami gets into the act now! Short ball to him, he opens up a bit and pulls it handsomely over the midwicket boundary for another six, the second of the innings
on the other side this time! This one was well outside off, Jadeja waited for it cut it late between short third man and backward point to pierce the gap for four

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: slower ball, Jadeja picks it and whips it for six! It came from the back of the hand, pitched outside leg and he rocked back to loft it with a pivot over the midwicket boundary for six!
in the block hole outside off, RJ makes some room to tap it to short third man and Samuels dives to save a few runs
bangs in the short ball towards leg side, Shami pulls it fine to fine leg for one
slower delivery down the leg side, another wide

commentPreTextItems.html: Third man brought in the circle

commentTextItems.html: yorker on the off stump, Shami makes room and digs it out to cover point
full and a bit wide, driven down a bit wide of long-off. There was a second there, probably, but Shami didn't look interested
full again and this one's flicked fine off the pads to fine leg for two more

headshotImage.caption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021
headshotImage.longCaption: Ravi Rampaul player page headshot cutout, 2021

commentTextItems.html: full and angled into the pads, Shami flicks by lifting his right leg to maintain the balance and plays the flamingo shot for four
shorter this time and angled in, Shami makes room again and misses it completely
he wants to pull, he makes room, but he doesn't get much and slaps it to mid-on
length ball outside off at 122kph give RJ enough time to punch it off the back foot
strays down the leg side for a wide with a full delivery and Ramdin can't collect it

commentPreTextItems.html: More praise for the visitors. Gaurav Reddy: "Only the West Indies cricket team can hammer the World Champions after twice getting thrashed twice by India 'A' in the same week! "

commentTextItems.html: back of length just outside off, Jadeja taps it softly on off for a quick one

dismissalComment.html: oh dear, he's rushed down the track and miscued a swipe to mid-on. He's showed some good timing till now and he seems to know it as he walks back, head thrown back, but this time he has looked to force a drill down the ground. To horrible effects
